      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(model-fallback): don't rethrow provider-side AbortErrors as user cancellations",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen the LLM API closes the connection mid-stream, the fetch layer surfaces `AbortError(\"This operation was aborted\")` with **no external abort signal triggered** (`externalAbort: false` in trajectory). The existing code treated *any* AbortError as a user/gateway cancellation, causing a silent failure chain in group/channel sessions.\n\n**Reproduction path (source inspection + confirmed by real trajectory):**\n\n1. Provider drops connection → `AbortError(\"This operation was aborted\")`, `promptErrorSource: \"prompt\"`, `externalAbort: false`\n2. `runFallbackCandidate`: `shouldRethrowAbort` = true (name === \"AbortError\"), `normalizedFailover` = null → **throws**, skipping all fallback candidates\n3. `agent-runner-execution.ts` catch: not a user/restart/draining abort → `buildExternalRunFailureReply` → `isGenericRunnerFailure: true`\n4. `resolveExternalRunFailureTextForConversation`: group/channel session + generic failure → **`SILENT_REPLY_TOKEN`**\n5. User receives **zero visible response**; every subsequent message in the same topic repeats the same path → topic is permanently silenced\n\n## Real behavior proof (redacted)\n\nTwo trajectory records from the affected installation (private details redacted):\n\n**Event 1 — 2026-06-06T02:14:27Z**\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"trace.artifacts\",\n  \"provider\": \"<provider>\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"finalStatus\": \"error\",\n    \"aborted\": true,\n    \"externalAbort\": false,\n    \"promptError\": \"This operation was aborted\",\n    \"promptErrorSource\": \"prompt\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Event 2 — 2026-06-06T09:02:28Z** (same session, subsequent message — confirms repeat-silence pattern)\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"trace.artifacts\",\n  \"provider\": \"<provider>\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"finalStatus\": \"error\",\n    \"aborted\": true,\n    \"externalAbort\": false,\n    \"promptError\": \"This operation was aborted\",\n    \"promptErrorSource\": \"prompt\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nBoth events: `externalAbort: false` confirms no external signal fired. Both resulted in `dispatch complete replies=0` in gateway logs (feishu channel, group conversation).\n\nAfter the fix, subsequent messages in the same topic replied normally — confirming the session was not permanently broken, only every individual turn that hit the provider-side abort was silenced.\n\n## Fix (addresses ClawSweeper P2 — no-fallback path also fixed)\n\n**Two-part fix covering both the fallback and no-fallback cases:**\n\n### Part 1 — `src/agents/model-fallback.ts`\nGate `shouldRethrowAbort` rethrow on `params.abortSignal?.aborted`:\n```diff\n-    if (shouldRethrowAbort(err) && !normalizedFailover) {\n+    // Only rethrow when external signal has actually fired (user/gateway cancel).\n+    // Provider-side AbortErrors (no signal) fall through to fallback/error reply.\n+    if (shouldRethrowAbort(err) && !normalizedFailover && params.abortSignal?.aborted) {\n       throw err;\n     }\n```\n→ With fallback configured: error enters fallback loop, tries next model.\n\n### Part 2 — `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-execution.ts`\nClear `isGenericRunnerFailure` flag for provider-side AbortErrors before `resolveExternalRunFailureTextForConversation`:\n```diff\n+    // Provider-side AbortError must not be silenced in group/channel sessions.\n+    isGenericRunnerFailure:\n+      (externalRunFailureReply?.isGenericRunnerFailure ?? false) &&\n+      !(isAbortError(err) && !(params.replyOperation?.result?.kind === \"aborted\")),\n-    isGenericRunnerFailure: externalRunFailureReply?.isGenericRunnerFailure ?? false,\n```\n→ Without fallback (or all candidates exhausted): user sees ⚠️ error message instead of silence.\n\n## Tests\n\n### `model-fallback.test.ts` (78 tests, all pass)\n- Updated `\"does not fall back on user aborts\"` → passes a pre-aborted signal (correct precondition for genuine user cancel)\n- Added `\"falls back when AbortError comes from the LLM provider (no external abort signal)\"` — proves fallback path taken\n\n### `agent-runner-execution.test.ts` (189 tests, all pass — +6 new)\n- Added `it.each(NON_DIRECT_FAILURE_SURFACE_CASES)(\"surfaces visible error (not SILENT_REPLY_TOKEN) for provider-side AbortError in $label chats\")` — 6 cases covering Discord group/channel, Slack channel, Telegram group, WhatsApp group, Teams channel\n\nBoth test files pass clean with `vitest run`.",
        "branch": "fix/abort-no-visible-reply-fallback",
